= render :partial => "home/slider"


.divider

%div#features.row
  %div.feature.four.columns
    = image_tag "people.png", :class => :people
    = render :partial => "coshx_blue_x", :locals => {:feature => "COMPANY"}
    %p{"data-action" => whereami, "data-index" => "10", "data-content" => "e"}
      Meet the team, find out why we're different - and why you should hire us to work your next website or other software project.
    = link_to about_path, :class => "a-button" do
      About Us
  %div.feature.four.columns
    = image_tag "services.png", :class => :gears
    = render :partial => "coshx_blue_x", :locals => {:feature => "SERVICES"}
    %p{"data-action" => whereami, "data-index" => "11", "data-content" => "e"}
      Whether you're an established enterprise or a boostrapping startup, we want to work with you. Take a look at the services we offer.
    = link_to services_path, :class => "a-button" do
      Our Services
  %div.feature.four.columns
    = image_tag "projects.png", :class => :beaker
    = render :partial => "coshx_blue_x", :locals => {:feature => "PROJECTS"}
    %p{"data-action" => whereami, "data-index" => "12", "data-content" => "e"}
      We've been fortunate enough to work on many great projects. Here's some highlights of the work we've done.
    = link_to projects_path, :class => "a-button" do
      Our Projects

.divider

%section#contact-us
  = image_tag "mail.png"
  %h2{"data-action" => whereami, "data-index" => "20", "data-content" => "e"}
    DON'T BE SHY, SAY HELLO

  %p{"data-action" => whereami, "data-index" => "21", "data-content" => "e"}
    Let's start up a conversation about what your needs are and how we can help. We're just a quick email away!

  -# Normally we'd use mail_to and not link_to for an email link, but this will eventually open a form, not be a mailto
  = link_to "mailto:info@coshx.com", :class => ["first", "a-button"] do
    Contact Us

  = link_to "mailto:info@coshx.com?subject=Coshx%20Labs%20quote%20request", :class => "a-button white" do
    Request a FREE Quote


= render :partial => "projects/list", :locals => {:featured_projects => @featured_projects}
  

.divider

=# render :partial => "clients/list", :locals => {:clients => @clients}
